headline: Lockheed Martin (LMT): Assessing Valuation Following Record $11B CH-53K Contract Win
summary: If you’ve been eyeing Lockheed Martin (LMT) lately, this latest news probably feels like a real turning point. Lockheed’s Sikorsky division just landed its largest contract ever for the CH-53K King Stallion helicopters—a nearly $11 billion multi-year deal with the U.S. Navy to deliver up to 99 units for the Marine Corps. The agreement combines several orders into one, locking in steady pricing and production while giving Lockheed a huge runway of confirmed business stretching into the next...
